              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/fiction/three-scenes-april-6-1939-moikom-zeqo" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Eagle-anchor_0.jpg?itok=B7QLAG78" width="250" height="175" alt="A photograph of an eagle&#039;s head, soaked in red tones" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/fiction/three-scenes-april-6-1939-moikom-zeqo">Three Scenes: April 6, 1939</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/moikom-zeqo" hreflang="en">Moikom Zeqo</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/fiction/good-enough-now-excerpt-jason-m-thornberry" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Thornberry-Anchor.jpg?itok=7PBU1nlE" width="250" height="175" alt="A photograph of a stack of boxes dimly lit by a window nearby" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

